WEBVTT

00:04.071 --> 00:09.421
The aim, when a filmmaker promotes a film, is to reach the maximum amount of people,...

00:09.969 --> 00:15.439
...so film producers invest astronomical amounts of money in promotional techniques.

00:16.574 --> 00:20.136
They want to capture and maintain the attention of audiences...

00:20.609 --> 00:22.885
...and they go to any lengths to achieve it.

00:23.935 --> 00:28.495
Through these huge promotions, investors hope to recover production costs.

00:29.570 --> 00:32.566
To achieve their ultimate goal of enticing the viewers,...

00:32.987 --> 00:37.273
..."CinemaScope", wide screen projection, and 3D were created.

00:38.329 --> 00:41.642
TV and radio also play an important role.

00:42.655 --> 00:46.850
Product placement, where clippings of films appear during TV shows,...

00:47.236 --> 00:52.302
...and extended placement, where talk shows discuss films and their technical part,...

00:52.755 --> 00:54.086
...are the techniques used.

00:55.237 --> 01:00.775
Another major technique is the virtual world, where you can see trailers of films.

01:01.823 --> 01:06.361
The traditional form of paid advertisement in newspapers and magazines...

01:06.702 --> 01:09.579
...is still a very important part of any campaign.

01:10.635 --> 01:14.001
Co - branding and co - advertising are also used.

01:15.076 --> 01:19.144
The film industry spends more than 2 billion dollars yearly in marketing.

01:20.152 --> 01:22.666
It costs a lot of money to make a film.

